11.Name: healeddata
11.SqlCommand:
WITH ResolvedWounds AS (
    -- Step 1: Resolve woundFk directly or by looking for it within the same patient and date
    SELECT 
        n.value,
        COALESCE(ass.woundFk, subass.woundFk) AS resolvedWoundFk, -- Assign woundFk
        ass.id AS assessmentId, -- Original assessment ID
        ass.dimdateFk, -- Original assessment date
        ass.patientFk -- Patient ID for the assessment
    FROM rpt.note n
    INNER JOIN rpt.AttributeType a ON n.attributetypefk = a.id
    INNER JOIN rpt.Assessment ass ON ass.id = n.assessmentFk
    LEFT JOIN rpt.Assessment subass 
        ON ass.dimdateFk = subass.dimdateFk 
           AND ass.patientFk = subass.patientFk -- Same patient
           AND subass.woundFk IS NOT NULL
    WHERE a.name LIKE '%Compression%'
),
HealedWounds AS (
    -- Step 2: Filter wounds whose current state is healed
    SELECT DISTINCT 
        w.id AS woundFk,
        ws.startDateDimDateFk AS healedDateFk -- Date when the wound was healed
    FROM rpt.Wound w
    INNER JOIN rpt.WoundState ws ON w.id = ws.woundFk
    INNER JOIN rpt.WoundStateType wst ON ws.woundstatetypeFk = wst.id
    WHERE ws.isCurrentState = 1 -- Current state
      AND wst.name = 'Resurfaced/Resolved' -- Healed state
),
CategorizedWounds AS (
    -- Step 3: Apply categorization based on the 'value' and join to dimdate table
    SELECT 
        rw.resolvedWoundFk AS woundFk,
        rw.value,
        rw.patientFk, -- Include the patientFk in the final result
        dd.date AS assessmentDate, -- Join to dimdate table and display the date column
        rw.assessmentId, -- Include the original assessment ID
        hws.healedDateFk, -- Include the healed date foreign key
        -- Add the 'new_value' column with categorization based on rw.value
        CASE 
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Coban II%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Multi%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Profore 3%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Circ%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Farrow%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Single Layer%' THEN 'High Compression'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Coban%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Coban Lite%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Profore 4%' THEN 'Reduced Compression'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Comprem%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Tubigrip%' THEN 'Tubular Elastic Bandage'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Compression Pump%' THEN 'Compression Pump'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Stocking%' THEN 'Compression Stockings'
            ELSE 'Other'
        END AS new_value -- Apply the categorization logic
    FROM ResolvedWounds rw
    INNER JOIN rpt.dimdate dd ON rw.dimdateFk = dd.id -- Join dimdate table on dimdateFk
    INNER JOIN HealedWounds hws ON rw.resolvedWoundFk = hws.woundFk -- Filter only healed wounds
    WHERE rw.resolvedWoundFk IS NOT NULL -- Ensure only valid woundFk entries
        AND CASE 
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Coban II%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Multi%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Profore 3%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Circ%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Farrow%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Single Layer%' THEN 'High Compression'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Coban%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Coban Lite%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Profore 4%' THEN 'Reduced Compression'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Comprem%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Tubigrip%' THEN 'Tubular Elastic Bandage'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Compression Pump%' THEN 'Compression Pump'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Stocking%' THEN 'Compression Stockings'
            ELSE 'Other'
        END != 'Other' -- Exclude 'Other' values
),
RankedWounds AS (
    -- Step 4: Rank the rows by assessmentDate for each woundFk
    SELECT * ,
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY woundFk ORDER BY assessmentDate) AS rn
    FROM CategorizedWounds
),
MostRecentEtiologies AS (
    -- Get the most recent etiology for each wound
    SELECT 
        n.woundFk AS woundId,
        n.patientFk AS patientId,
        n.value AS primaryEtiology,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY n.woundFk ORDER BY n.dimDateFk DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.Note AS n
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AttributeType AS atr 
        ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE 
        atr.name = 'Primary Etiology'
    AND n.value='Venous Leg Ulcer/VLU'
)
-- Final Query: Combine RankedWounds and MostRecentEtiologies
SELECT 
    rw.woundFk,
    rw.value,
    rw.patientFk,
    rw.assessmentDate,
    rw.assessmentId,
    rw.new_value,
    healedDimDate.date AS healedDate, -- Convert the healed date foreign key to a readable date
    DATEDIFF(DAY, rw.assessmentDate, healedDimDate.date) AS daysToHeal, -- Calculate the difference in days
    -- Categorize daysToHeal into brackets
    CASE 
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, rw.assessmentDate, healedDimDate.date) <= 60 THEN '0-2 months'
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, rw.assessmentDate, healedDimDate.date) <= 120 THEN '2-4 months'
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, rw.assessmentDate, healedDimDate.date) <= 180 THEN '4-6 months'
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, rw.assessmentDate, healedDimDate.date) <= 240 THEN '6-8 months'
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, rw.assessmentDate, healedDimDate.date) <= 300 THEN '8-10 months'
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, rw.assessmentDate, healedDimDate.date) <= 365 THEN '10-12 months'
        ELSE '12+ months'
    END AS healingBracket, -- Healing time bracket
    mre.primaryEtiology -- Include the most recent primary etiology
FROM RankedWounds rw
INNER JOIN rpt.dimdate healedDimDate ON rw.healedDateFk = healedDimDate.id -- Join to get the healed date
LEFT JOIN MostRecentEtiologies mre ON rw.woundFk = mre.woundId AND mre.RowNum = 1 -- Join to get the most recent etiology
WHERE rw.rn = 1 -- Filter to get the earliest row for each woundFk
AND mre.rowNum=1
ORDER BY rw.patientFk, rw.woundFk, rw.assessmentDate;

12.Name: total VLU's using compression
12.SqlCommand:
WITH ResolvedWounds AS (
    -- Step 1: Resolve woundFk for assessments related to compression
    SELECT 
        COALESCE(ass.woundFk, subass.woundFk) AS resolvedWoundFk,
        ass.patientFk,
        ass.dimdateFk,  -- Include the dimdateFk for sorting by date
        ass.id AS assessmentId,
        n.value -- Include the value from the note table (should be n.value)
    FROM rpt.note n
    INNER JOIN rpt.AttributeType a ON n.attributetypefk = a.id
    INNER JOIN rpt.Assessment ass ON ass.id = n.assessmentFk
    LEFT JOIN rpt.Assessment subass 
        ON ass.dimdateFk = subass.dimdateFk 
           AND ass.patientFk = subass.patientFk 
           AND subass.woundFk IS NOT NULL
    WHERE a.name LIKE '%Compression%'
),

VenousLegUlcers AS (
    -- Step 2: Identify all VLUs
    SELECT DISTINCT 
        n.woundFk AS woundId,
        n.patientFk AS patientId
    FROM rpt.Note AS n
    INNER JOIN rpt.AttributeType AS atr ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE atr.name = 'Primary Etiology'
      AND n.value = 'Venous Leg Ulcer/VLU'
),

CompressionVLUs AS (
    -- Step 3: Combine resolved wounds with VLUs
    SELECT DISTINCT 
        vlu.woundId,
        vlu.patientId
    FROM ResolvedWounds rw
    INNER JOIN VenousLegUlcers vlu 
        ON rw.resolvedWoundFk = vlu.woundId
),

CategorizedWounds AS (
    -- Step 4: Categorize the wounds based on 'value' and find the earliest one
    SELECT 
        rw.resolvedWoundFk AS woundFk,
        rw.patientFk,
        rw.assessmentId,
        dd.date AS assessmentDate,
        rw.dimdateFk,
        rw.value, -- Include value here
        CASE 
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Coban II%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Multi%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Profore 3%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Circ%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Farrow%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Single Layer%' THEN 'High Compression'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Coban%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Coban Lite%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Profore 4%' THEN 'Reduced Compression'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Comprem%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Tubigrip%' THEN 'Tubular Elastic Bandage'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Compression Pump%' THEN 'Compression Pump'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Stocking%' THEN 'Compression Stockings'
            ELSE 'Other'
        END AS compressionType,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY rw.resolvedWoundFk ORDER BY dd.date ASC) AS RowNum  -- Earliest first
    FROM ResolvedWounds rw
    INNER JOIN rpt.dimdate dd ON rw.dimdateFk = dd.id
    WHERE rw.resolvedWoundFk IS NOT NULL
        AND CASE 
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Coban II%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Multi%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Profore 3%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Circ%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Farrow%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Single Layer%' THEN 'High Compression'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Coban%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Coban Lite%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Profore 4%' THEN 'Reduced Compression'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Comprem%' OR rw.value LIKE '%Tubigrip%' THEN 'Tubular Elastic Bandage'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Compression Pump%' THEN 'Compression Pump'
            WHEN rw.value LIKE '%Stocking%' THEN 'Compression Stockings'
            ELSE 'Other'
        END != 'Other'  -- Exclude 'Other'
),

MostRecentEtiologies AS (
    -- Step 5: Fetch the most recent primary etiologies
    SELECT 
        n.woundFk,
        n.patientFk,
        n.value AS primaryEtiology,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY n.woundFk ORDER BY n.dimDateFk DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM rpt.Note n
    INNER JOIN rpt.AttributeType atr ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE atr.name = 'Primary Etiology'
    AND n.value = 'Venous Leg Ulcer/VLU'
)

-- Final Query: Get the earliest compression type and the most recent primary etiology for each wound
SELECT 
    cv.woundFk,
    cv.patientFk,
    cv.compressionType,
    cv.assessmentDate,
    mre.primaryEtiology
FROM CategorizedWounds cv
INNER JOIN MostRecentEtiologies mre 
    ON cv.woundFk = mre.woundFk AND mre.RowNum = 1  -- Join on the most recent primary etiology
WHERE cv.RowNum = 1  -- Only the earliest compression
ORDER BY cv.patientFk, cv.woundFk;

13.Name: total VLUS
13.SqlCommand:
WITH MostRecentPrimary AS (
        SELECT
        n.woundFk,
        n.patientFk,
        n.value AS primaryEtiology,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY n.woundFk ORDER BY n.dimDateFk DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM rpt.Note n
    INNER JOIN rpt.AttributeType atr ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE atr.name = 'Primary Etiology'
    AND n.value='Venous Leg Ulcer/VLU'
)

SELECT * FROM MostRecentPrimary mrp WHERE mrp.rownum=1;
